articles.description: Kameron Chatman had his ninth double-double of the season with 26 points and 11 rebounds to help Detroit Mercy beat Youngstown State 94-84 on Friday night.
articles.headline: Detroit Mercy outlasts Youngstown State 94-84

articles.description: Louisville hosts No. 14 North Carolina on Saturday night in what is likely the Cardinals' biggest home game of the season.
articles.headline: Louisville seeks signature win vs. No. 14 UNC

articles.description: No. 18 Tennessee bounced back from its worst performance in months with a hard-fought win over South Carolina on Wednesday.
articles.headline: No. 18 Tennessee tries to keep rolling at Georgia

articles.description: A   A week ago, Saint Mary's was riding the nation's longest winning streak at 19 games, heading toward a probable No. 2 seed in the NCAA Tournament and sitting on top of the West Coast Conference standings getting ready for a showdown with arch-rival...
articles.headline: Saint Mary's hopes to end skid against Portland

articles.description: No. 10 Auburn defeated Kentucky by 10 points on Valentine's Day, making Tigers coach Bruce Pearl love leading scorer Bryce Brown even more heading into Saturday's game at South Carolina.
articles.headline: Auburn looks to keep rolling against South Carolina

articles.description: It's been a historic season for the Xavier, but as the No. 4 Musketeers try to lock down their first Big East Conference title and a possible No. 1 seed in the NCAA Tournament, they'll have to find a way to topple No. 3 Villanova on Saturday afternoon...
articles.headline: No. 4 Xavier hosts No. 3 Villanova in marquee clash

videos.description: The Gators trurn the ball over but Kevarrius Hayes chases down Jonathan Williams and blocks his shot at the rim.
videos.headline: Florida's Hayes gets a great chase-down block

videos.description: Johnathan Williams dishes a nice assist to Killian Tillie and he throws down the hammer for the bucket.
videos.headline: Gonzaga's Tillie throws down nasty dunk

videos.description: Josh Perkins lobs it to Johnathan Williams and he dunks all over his defender.
videos.headline: Gonzaga's Williams puts defender on a poster

videos.description: Chris Chiozza cuts to the ball and takes it up strong against the defender for the and-1.
videos.headline: Florida's Chiozza finishes strong in the lane

videos.description: Josh Perkins draws the defender on the screen then dishes a nice pass to Johnathan Williams for the dunk.
videos.headline: Bulldogs' Perkins-Williams connection leads to dunk

videos.description: Josh Perkins crosses his defender then drills the three-pointer right before the buzzer.
videos.headline: Gonzaga's Perkins makes a nice move and hits the shot

videos.description: Josh Perkins hesitates then bursts to the basket and finishes through contact for the bucket.
videos.headline: Gonzaga's Perkins gets clutch and-1

videos.description: Gonzaga and Florida trade a trio of buckets, resulting in the game being tied at 95-95 and heading to double overtime.
videos.headline: Wild sequence only leads to tie game

videos.description: Jalen Hudson drills two clutch threes in double overtime to push Florida to a 111-105 win against Gonzaga.
videos.headline: Hudson's pair of 3's leads Florida to big win
